        h1("Abstract"),
        p("HireAI is an intelligent, AI-powered job portal developed as part of the Final Year Project at Bahria University, Karachi Campus. The platform is engineered to address three critical, persistent failures in conventional recruitment systems: the Vocabulary Mismatch problem in resume-to-job matching, the prevalence of Algorithmic Bias in candidate ranking, and the absence of Explainability in AI-driven hiring decisions — commonly referred to as the Black Box problem."),
        p("Built on a MERN stack (MongoDB, Express.js, React.js, Node.js) foundation with a Python FastAPI microservice layer for AI processing, HireAI introduces a Semantic Intelligence Engine grounded in the ESCO (European Skills, Competences, Qualifications and Occupations) taxonomy to semantically map synonymous skills and achieve context-aware candidate matching. The platform further implements a Fairness-Aware Ranking (FAR) algorithm using IBM AIF360 and Microsoft FairLearn to ensure demographic parity across candidate shortlisting, targeting a Four-Fifths Rule compliance ratio greater than 0.8."),
        p("A key innovation of HireAI is its Explainable AI (XAI) Engine, which generates counterfactual explanations for match scores, enabling candidates to understand precisely why they were or were not matched and what specific skill acquisitions would improve their standing. The platform also features a Hybrid Job Discovery Engine that seamlessly aggregates real-time job listings from external platforms (LinkedIn, Indeed, Glassdoor) via the JSearch API alongside internally posted positions, offering users a unified job market view."),
