        h1("Chapter 7: Conclusion and Future Work"),

        h2("7.1 Conclusion"),
        p("HireAI successfully delivers a production-ready, AI-powered recruitment platform that addresses three critical and previously unresolved failures in conventional job portal systems: the Vocabulary Mismatch problem, Algorithmic Bias in candidate ranking, and Black Box rejection with no feedback. Through the integration of four purpose-built AI modules — the Semantic Intelligence Engine, the Explainable AI Engine, the Fairness-Aware Ranking module, and the Resume Analyzer with ATS scoring — HireAI advances the state of practice in intelligent recruitment beyond what any single commercial platform currently offers."),
        p("The platform achieves all defined success criteria: a semantic synonym-matching accuracy of 87.3% (target: 85%), a demographic parity ratio of 0.83 (target: 0.80), an AI inference time of 1.4 seconds (target: <2 seconds), and a zero-cost deployment architecture. The Hybrid Job Discovery Engine provides users with a unified interface to both internally posted jobs and real-time listings from major external platforms, addressing the platform fragmentation problem without requiring direct API partnerships with LinkedIn or Indeed."),
        p("The project was completed by a three-person team of BSE-7C students at Bahria University, Karachi Campus, under the supervision of Engr. Zoobia Zeeshan, within a 29-week development timeline and a $0 budget constraint. The team demonstrated competency across the full modern software engineering stack — from React frontend architecture through Node.js API development to Python AI microservice implementation — delivering a system of research-grade AI sophistication within a practical, usable application."),
        p("HireAI contributes to United Nations SDGs 4, 8, 9, and 10 by improving equitable access to employment opportunities, supporting skill development and lifelong learning, modernizing recruitment infrastructure through AI, and actively mitigating bias in hiring to reduce employment inequality."),

        h2("7.2 Limitations"),
        p("The following limitations are acknowledged:"),
        bullet("The Semantic Intelligence Engine's ESCO taxonomy coverage is strongest for the European and Western labor market context. Skill terminology specific to the Pakistani market may have lower coverage in the initial taxonomy subset, though the system's embedding-based fallback provides partial mitigation."),
        bullet("The Fairness-Aware Ranking module infers protected attribute proxies for fairness monitoring, as directly collecting gender or demographic data raises ethical and legal concerns. Proxy-based inference introduces potential inaccuracy in fairness measurements."),
        bullet("The JSearch API dependency introduces an external failure point and API quota limitation. Usage of the free tier limits total monthly external job searches, which may degrade the External Mode experience under high traffic."),
        bullet("The AI Chatbot's quality is bounded by the underlying LLM API's capabilities and rate limits. During periods of high API load, response times may exceed the target threshold."),
        bullet("UAT was conducted with a limited sample (10 job seekers, 3 employers) from a single university context, limiting the generalizability of usability findings."),

        h2("7.3 Future Work"),
        p("The following enhancements are identified for future development phases:"),
        numbered("AI Video Mock Interviews: Integration of computer vision and speech analysis to provide real-time feedback on verbal and non-verbal communication during simulated job interviews, addressing the growing trend of AI-assisted interview screening."),
        numbered("Salary Prediction Engine: Development of a machine learning regression model trained on publicly available salary datasets (supplemented by Glassdoor and PayScale API integrations) to provide role- and location-specific salary range predictions for both job seekers and employers."),
        numbered("E-Learning Integration: Direct API integration with Coursera and Udemy to surface relevant, purchasable courses within the Skill Gap Analysis panel, closing the loop between skill gap identification and skill acquisition."),
        numbered("Pakistani Market Taxonomy Expansion: Extension of the ESCO skill knowledge graph with Pakistan-specific skill terminology and job market vocabulary, in collaboration with HEC and local industry partners."),
        numbered("Multi-Language Support: Extension of the platform interface and NLP pipeline to Urdu, enabling broader accessibility for Pakistani job seekers whose primary language is not English."),
        numbered("Employer Verified Badge System: Implementation of a verification pipeline for employer company profiles, using business registration data, to increase trust and reduce fraudulent job postings."),
        numbered("Advanced Analytics for Employers: Development of a predictive hiring analytics module that forecasts applicant quality and volume for a given job posting based on historical platform data, enabling more informed job posting strategies."),
        numbered("Mobile Application: Development of native iOS and Android applications to extend HireAI's reach to the mobile-first user segments that dominate internet access in Pakistan."),

