        p("Research indicates that keyword-based matching systems produce high rates of false negatives where genuinely qualified candidates are filtered out due to terminological differences. A candidate listing 'TensorFlow' may not match a job requiring 'Machine Learning' despite clear conceptual overlap. Similarly, recruiters face overwhelming application volumes with little automated intelligence to assist in objective, fair, and efficient shortlisting processes. The absence of explainability in AI-assisted hiring systems has drawn growing scrutiny from ethicists, regulators, and applicants who deserve transparent insight into automated decisions affecting their livelihoods."),

        p("HireAI was conceived and developed as a Final Year Project at Bahria University, Karachi Campus, to systematically address these structural deficiencies in contemporary recruitment technology. The platform reframes recruitment as a semantic understanding and fairness-enforcement problem rather than a surface-level keyword matching exercise, introducing decision transparency through counterfactual explanations and enforcing demographic equity through algorithmic fairness safeguards."),

