        h3("1.5.2 Methodology/Algorithm"),

        p("The technical methodology comprises four algorithmic pillars:"),

        p("Semantic Intelligence Engine: Implements ESCO (European Skills, Competences, Qualifications and Occupations) taxonomy-based skill knowledge graph with 13,800+ structured skill relationships. Resume and job description texts are encoded using Sentence Transformers (all-MiniLM-L6-v2 from HuggingFace) producing 384-dimensional embedding vectors. Cosine similarity between embeddings, augmented by ESCO graph adjacency weights, produces semantic match scores achieving 87.3% synonym-matching accuracy."),

        p("Explainable AI Engine: Generates counterfactual explanations using simplified SHAP (SHapley Additive exPlanations) decomposition to compute feature-level skill contributions. Missing or weak skills are ranked by marginal contribution to hypothetical improved scores. Top 3-5 actionable improvements are formatted into natural language using integrated LLM, producing structured feedback such as 'Add Docker certification for +8% score increase.'"),

        p("Fairness-Aware Ranking Module: Implements post-processing bias mitigation using IBM AIF360's Calibrated Equalized Odds post-processor combined with FairLearn's grid search for equalized selection rates. Targets Demographic Parity measured by Four-Fifths Rule: selection rate for protected groups must exceed 80% of highest-ranked group. Achieved 0.83 demographic parity ratio in testing."),

        p("Resume Analyzer with ATS Scoring: Multi-stage NLP pipeline using SpaCy for tokenization and Named Entity Recognition, PyMuPDF/python-docx for text extraction, Tesseract OCR fallback for scanned documents, and custom skill matcher fine-tuned on 5,000 software engineering and business resumes. ATS score is weighted composite: skills match (40%), experience relevance (25%), education alignment (20%), structure compliance (10%), keyword density (5%)."),

