      p("Our evaluation showed that the system achieves around 84.7% semantic matching accuracy, successfully brings fairness scores above the 0.8 threshold in all tested categories, handles over 12,000 concurrent users without performance issues, and significantly improves how useful and trustworthy candidates find the application experience."),

      p("We are pretty proud of what we built but we also know there is a lot more that could be done. For future work we would like to improve the ESCO coverage for non-technical job categories like Product Management and Business, add a video mock interview feature, and look into training a custom language model on recruitment data rather than using general-purpose GPT for the explanations."),

      p("HireAI is a proof of concept that shows it is possible to build a fairer, smarter, and more transparent recruitment platform without needing to abandon the familiar job portal experience that users are already comfortable with."),

      gap(),

      // ─── ACKNOWLEDGMENT ───────────────────────────────────────────────
      h1("Acknowledgment"),

      p("We would like to thank our FYP supervisor Engr. Zoobia Zeeshan for her continuous guidance and feedback throughout this project. We also thank the Department of Software Engineering at Bahria University Karachi Campus for providing us with the resources and opportunity to work on this project."),

      gap(),

      // ─── REFERENCES ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
      h1("References"),

      ...[
        "[1]  M. Nikolaou, \"AI in Recruitment: The Future of Hiring,\" IEEE Transactions on Engineering Management, vol. 68, no. 4, pp. 1102–1114, 2021.",
        "[2]  A. Köchling and M. C. Wehner, \"Discriminated by an Algorithm: A Systematic Review of Discrimination and Fairness by Algorithmic Decision-Making in the Context of HR Recruitment,\" Business Research, vol. 13, no. 3, pp. 795–848, 2020.",
